OL,3,CUK not ready to fight an all-out war
OL,4,Cdue to 'overstretched' army, MPs warn
OL,6,F"On top of this, the high tempo of
OL,7,Foperations and unrelenting pressure on
OL,8,Four services has led to a drop in
OL,9,Fretention, compounded by a period of
OL,10,Flow recruitment and difficulties
OL,11,Fintroducing and maintaining
OL,12,Fcapabilities, thereby creating a
OL,13,Fvicious cycle."
OL,15,FHe said the government must fully
OL,16,Finvest in the military.
OL,18,FEfforts by the Ministry of Defence
OL,19,F(MoD) to tackle the problem are not
OL,20,F"being carried out at the required
OL,21,Fpace", the report said.
